devdoc.details: All function calls are currently implemented without side effects

newVote(uint256,uint256,address,uint256,.details: Creates an event after counting the votes on propsal

params.proposal: Id of theProposal on which user wants to vote on

proposalCount(uint256,bool).details: Creates an event after counting the votes on propsal

params.passed: Result of the voting on proposal, passed defines that the proposal is accepted by the voters

proposalCreated(uint256,string,uint256,a.details: Creates an event after creating a new Proposal

params.maxVotes: Max Votes allowed on the proposal

addTokenId(uint256).details: Only Owner of the contract can add the Proposer to the Valid Tokens list

params._tokenId: NFT token id of the Proposer

countVotes(uint256).details: Only Owner can count votes of the proposal, function compares Votes Down and Votes Up with min 50% to favour the vote. Count can be performed only once.

createProposal(string,address[]).details: Initializes the proposal object and increment the index for next Proposal

params._canVote: CanVote array of the porposal to confirm the voters eligibility

voteOnProposal(uint256,bool).details: Check the eligibility of the voter for the proposal and updates the votes

params._vote: Vote from the user up or down, true or false
